Tennille Banking Company Building is a historic structure in Tennille, Georgia. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places on July 28, 1994. It is located at 102-104 North Main Street. The Tennille Banking Company opened in 1900. The building was designed by Charles E. Choate (August 31, 1865 â€“ 1929) who lived for ten years in Tennille.
